excerpt: Extensive collection of surrealist art by Salvador Dalí housed in a building with 900 glass panels.
detail_description: The Dalí Museum in St. Petersburg is a must-visit for art enthusiasts. The museum houses an extensive collection of surrealist art by Salvador Dalí and is known for its unique building with 900 glass panels. Visitors can also experience Dali 360, a captivating 30-minute projection dome show that brings the artist's works to life.
name: The Dalí Museum
address: 1 Dali Blvd, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Tropical, century-old attraction featuring thousands of plants, a butterfly aviary & flamingos.
detail_description: Sunken Gardens, located just outside downtown St. Petersburg, is a century-old tropical paradise featuring over 50,000 exotic plants and birds from around the world. This botanical gem also includes a traditional Japanese koi pond, sparkling waterfalls, and a pollinator garden filled with native Florida butterflies. Visitors can stroll past colorful macaws, cockatoos, kookaburras, and flamingos while learning about the gardens' fascinating history dating back to the 1950s.
name: Sunken Gardens
address: 1825 4th St N, St. Petersburg, FL 33704, USA

excerpt: Picturesque waterfront pier hosting 26 acres of water sports, parks, restaurants & outdoor concerts.
detail_description: St. Pete Pier is a charming waterfront destination that offers 26 acres of entertainment, including water sports, parks, restaurants, and outdoor concerts. The pedestrian-friendly area is lined with trees and features a variety of shops and dining options leading to the city's expansive waterfront. Visitors can admire the impressive "Bending Arc" sculpture by local artist Janet Echelman and enjoy family-friendly attractions such as the Majeed Foundation splash pad and a pirate-themed playground.
name: St. Pete Pier
address: 600 2nd Ave NE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Beaches, camping, trails & a historic fort in a vast park spread over multiple connected islands.
detail_description: Fort De Soto Park is a sprawling and historic park located in Pinellas County, Florida. It spans multiple connected islands and offers a diverse range of attractions. Visitors can explore nature trails, mangroves, and sand dunes adorned with yellow sunflowers. The park features seven miles of waterfront, two fishing piers, and a 120-year-old fort built during the Spanish-American War.
name: Fort De Soto Park
address: Florida, USA

excerpt: Exhibits spanning 4,000 years, including African art, European paintings & American photography.
detail_description: The Museum of Fine Arts in St. Petersburg, Florida offers a diverse collection of exhibits spanning 4,000 years, featuring African art, European paintings, and American photography. The museum's stunning two-story glass conservatory overlooks the water and is surrounded by Spanish-style gardens and a popular park. It is a sought-after venue for weddings and events due to its picturesque setting. With 20,000 objects in its permanent collection and rotating exhibitions, the museum caters to various interests.
name: Museum of Fine Arts
address: 255 Beach Dr NE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Nonprofit museum offering 18,000 sq. ft. of hands-on exhibits & workshops aimed at kids.
detail_description: Great Explorations Children's Museum in St. Petersburg is a nonprofit museum that offers 18,000 sq. ft. of hands-on exhibits and workshops designed for kids. It is a top family attraction and learning center in the state, providing an inviting environment for children to engage with interactive displays and activities.
name: Great Explorations Children's Museum
address: 1925 4th St N, St. Petersburg, FL 33704, USA

excerpt: St. Pete Beach is a Florida resort city set on a barrier island, west of St. Petersburg. It’s known for its beaches. A 1928 landmark, the pink Moorish-style Don CeSar Hotel looms over the shore. The Pass-A-Grille area offers galleries, shops and the Gulf Beaches Historical Museum, which displays postcards and other artifacts in a 1917 church. Nearby, boats depart to Shell Key, a nesting site for seabirds and turtles.
detail_description: St. Pete Beach is a charming Florida resort city located on a barrier island, renowned for its stunning beaches and the iconic pink Moorish-style Don CeSar Hotel. The Pass-A-Grille area offers art galleries, shops, and the Gulf Beaches Historical Museum housed in a historic church. Visitors can embark on boat trips to Shell Key, a sanctuary for seabirds and turtles.
name: St Pete Beach
address: Florida, USA

excerpt: Fresh produce, prepared foods, plants & crafts sold at a vibrant weekly market with live bands.
detail_description: The St. Petersburg Saturday Morning Market is a lively weekly event that transforms downtown St. Pete into a vibrant hub of activity. This bustling farmers market, recognized as one of the largest in the Southeast U.S., offers an array of fresh produce, prepared foods, and unique crafts from local artisans. As you stroll through the market, you'll be greeted by live music that adds to the festive atmosphere—it's like a daytime celebration where shopping feels more like a party with friends!
name: St. Petersburg Saturday Morning Market
address: Williams Park, 350 2nd Ave N, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Contemporary art gallery showcasing local & international work & offering classes & workshops.
detail_description: The Morean Arts Center in St. Petersburg, FL is a contemporary art gallery that showcases the works of local and international artists. While it doesn't feature Dali's artwork, it focuses on displaying the talents of local and national artists, with occasional international features. The center also houses a permanent collection of Dale Chihuly's work and manages the Chihuly Collection.
name: Morean Arts Center
address: 719 Central Ave, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Contemporary gallery showcasing works by American emerging & established studio glass artists.
detail_description: Imagine Museum is a contemporary gallery featuring a diverse collection of works by both emerging and established American studio glass artists. The museum offers an immersive experience, inviting visitors to imagine stories, emotions, and ideas through the captivating glass art on display. From intricate infinity mirror pieces to thought-provoking boat-like sculptures by Swedish artist Bertil Vallien, the museum showcases the versatility of glass as a medium for artistic expression. Additionally, St.
name: Imagine Museum: Contemporary glass art
address: 1901 Central Ave, St. Petersburg, FL 33713, USA

excerpt: Natural retreat with abundant wildlife, trails, picnic areas, a gift shop & scenic tram tours.
detail_description: Boyd Hill Nature Preserve in St. Petersburg, Florida, is a 245-acre natural sanctuary offering a peaceful retreat from the city. Visitors can explore winding trails through diverse ecosystems like pine flatwoods and freshwater marshes while observing native wildlife such as alligators, bald eagles, and gopher tortoises. The preserve also offers scenic tram tours with knowledgeable guides providing insights into the area's natural beauty and habitats.
name: Boyd Hill Nature Preserve
address: 1101 Country Club Way S, St. Petersburg, FL 33705, USA

excerpt: Unique sculptures by legendary glass artist Dale Chihuly, plus glass-blowing demonstrations.
detail_description: The Chihuly Collection is a unique display of sculptures created by the renowned glass artist Dale Chihuly. The collection features vibrant and intricate glass pieces, including large-scale chandeliers that create a carnival-like atmosphere. Visitors can witness live glass-blowing demonstrations at the Morean Glass Studio, providing insight into the technical skill and artistry behind each piece. This museum offers a breathtaking exhibit of color and light, showcasing the storytelling potential of blown glass artistry through its diverse and stunning displays.
name: Chihuly Collection
address: 720 Central Ave, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: St. Petersburg is a city on Florida's gulf coast, part of the Tampa Bay area. It's known for its pleasant weather (hence its “Sunshine City” nickname), making it popular for golfing, boating, fishing and beachgoing. Its waterfront parks host the Dali Museum, featuring surrealist works of art; the Museum of Fine Arts, with works ranging from ancient to contemporary; and Mahaffey Theater, home of the Florida Orchestra.
detail_description: St. Petersburg, also known as "The Sunshine City," is a popular destination on Florida's gulf coast. The city boasts pleasant weather and offers a variety of outdoor activities such as golfing, boating, fishing, and beachgoing. Visitors can explore its waterfront parks which are home to renowned cultural institutions like the Dali Museum and the Museum of Fine Arts. St.
name: St. Petersburg
address: Florida, USA

excerpt: This museum documents the Holocaust, with special emphasis on the stories of local survivors.
detail_description: The Florida Holocaust Museum stands as a poignant reminder of the atrocities faced during the Holocaust, with a particular focus on local survivors' narratives. This museum offers an immersive experience through its meticulously curated collection of artifacts, photographs, artwork, and videos that delve into this harrowing chapter of history. A significant highlight is Boxcar #113 069-5, one of the few remaining railroad cars used by the Nazis for transporting victims to extermination camps like Auschwitz and Treblinka.
name: The Florida Holocaust Museum
address: 55 5th St S, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: 3,190-acre nature reserve with hiking paths, birdwatching, a paddling trail & canoe/kayak rentals.
detail_description: Weedon Island Preserve is a vast 3,190-acre nature reserve situated in north St. Petersburg along the shores of Tampa Bay. It offers a range of outdoor activities such as hiking, birdwatching, and paddling along designated trails for canoes and kayaks. Visitors can explore the diverse aquatic and upland ecosystems through nearly five miles of paths and boardwalks on foot or by water.
name: Weedon Island Preserve
address: 1800 Weedon Dr NE, St. Petersburg, FL 33702, USA

excerpt: Home of the Tampa Bay Rays, this stadium features the Rays Touch Tank & a baseball museum.
detail_description: Tropicana Field is the home of the Tampa Bay Rays and offers visitors the chance to see the Rays Touch Tank and a baseball museum. Located in downtown St. Petersburg, it is surrounded by cultural attractions such as museums, theaters, and parks. Nearby accommodations include elegantly appointed guestrooms with modern amenities like high-speed internet access and complimentary newspapers. Additionally, there are apartment options within walking distance of Tropicana Field that offer recreational facilities like a fitness center and a pool.
name: Tropicana Field
address: 1 Tropicana Dr., St. Petersburg, FL 33705, USA

excerpt: Park featuring waterfront views & 11+ acres of open space, plus room for various special events.
detail_description: Vinoy Park is a stunning 11+ acre waterfront park in St. Petersburg, offering picturesque views of Tampa Bay and the Pier. It's an ideal spot for picnics, outdoor activities, and special events like Ribfest and concerts. The park features a fitness center, dog park, walking paths, tennis courts, and various recreational amenities. Visitors can also enjoy sunrise yoga on the beach while taking in scenic ocean and city views.
name: Vinoy Park
address: 701 Bayshore Dr NE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Just west of Downtown, Historic Kenwood is a diverse, artsy district known for its mature oak trees, brick streets, and high concentration of Craftsman bungalows. Relaxed restaurants and cafes, beer bars, and gay nightspots line busy Central Avenue and 34 Street North. Neighborhood events like architecture tours and artist open-studio nights create a strong community vibe, and the LGBTQ Welcome Center is nearby.
detail_description: Historic Kenwood, located just west of Downtown, is a vibrant and diverse district renowned for its mature oak trees, brick streets, and abundance of Craftsman bungalows. The area boasts a lively atmosphere with relaxed restaurants, cafes, beer bars, and gay nightspots along Central Avenue and 34 Street North. Community events such as architecture tours and artist open-studio nights contribute to the strong sense of community in the neighborhood. Additionally, visitors can explore the LGBTQ Welcome Center nearby.
name: Historic Kenwood
address: St. Petersburg, FL, USA

excerpt: Panoramic drives & views over Lower Tampa Bay, with an adjoining beach & popular spots for angling.
detail_description: The Sunshine Skyway Bridge in St. Petersburg, FL offers a scenic drive with stunning views of Lower Tampa Bay. It's a popular spot for fishing and also provides access to nearby attractions like the Salvador Dali Museum and Tropicana Field for baseball games. The bridge, constructed in the late 1980s, spans over 4 miles and reaches heights of 190 feet above the water to accommodate boat traffic below.
name: Sunshine Skyway Bridge
address: 7508-7534 Sunshine Skyway Ln S, St. Petersburg, FL 33711, USA

excerpt: City's history museum with artifacts, photos & an exhibit on the beginning of commercial air travel.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of downtown, the St. Petersburg Museum of History is a treasure trove that chronicles the vibrant past of this charming city known as Sunshine City. For over a century, it has been dedicated to showcasing significant local stories, from the dawn of commercial aviation to Major League Baseball's spring training traditions. Visitors can marvel at an eclectic array of exhibits featuring everything from a two-headed calf and an ancient Egyptian mummy to a working replica of the Benoist XIV airboat.
name: St. Petersburg Museum of History
address: 335 2nd Ave NE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Gallery displaying contemporary Western, Native American, frontier & wildlife paintings & sculpture.
detail_description: The James Museum of Western & Wildlife Art in downtown St. Petersburg, FL is a captivating gallery showcasing contemporary Western, Native American, frontier, and wildlife art. The museum's exterior features meticulously placed sandstone blocks resembling artistically designed cliffs. Inside, visitors are greeted by a two-story waterfall and over 26,000 square feet of exhibit space dedicated to preserving traditional Old West American folk art.
name: The James Museum of Western & Wildlife Art
address: 150 Central Ave, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Craft brewery specializing in IPAs & ales, serving the suds in its taproom & large beer garden.
detail_description: Green Bench Brewing Company, named after the iconic green benches that once lined St. Petersburg's streets, is a craft brewery that has been a part of the city's beer scene since 2013. The brewery specializes in IPAs and ales and offers its brews in a taproom and large beer garden. It was one of the first to arrive on the craft brewery scene in St. Pete, followed by other local favorites like St. Pete Brewing Company and Cycle breweries.
name: Green Bench Brewing Company
address: 1133 Baum Ave N, St. Petersburg, FL 33705, USA

detail_description: Mazzaro's Italian Market has been a staple in St. Petersburg for nearly 30 years, offering an authentic Italian experience. It is a one-stop shop for all things Italian, from coffee and wine to cured meats, cheeses, handmade pasta, pizza, bread, pastries, and gelato. The market boasts the largest selection of Italian wines in Florida.
name: Mazzaro's Italian Market
address: 2909 22nd Ave N, St. Petersburg, FL 33713, USA

excerpt: Rustic-chic spot offering Cuban sandwiches, Latin American platters & specialty juices & smoothies.
detail_description: Bodega on Central is a popular spot in St. Petersburg, offering a rustic-chic ambiance and serving Cuban sandwiches, Latin American platters, specialty juices, and smoothies. It's part of the modern dining scene in the city, catering to local residents rather than tourists. The family-owned restaurant with Brooklyn roots provides traditional street-style outdoor dining in downtown St. Pete.
name: Bodega on Central
address: 1180 Central Ave, St. Petersburg, FL 33705, USA

excerpt: Wildlife preserve on an undeveloped island with camping available by permit & nature activities.
detail_description: Shell Key Preserve is a 1,828-acre wildlife preserve located in the mouth of Tampa Bay, featuring a 195-acre barrier island known as Shell Key. Accessible only by boat, this undeveloped island offers camping permits and various nature activities. Visitors can kayak through mangrove tunnels, explore sandbars, and spot abundant marine life. Guided tours are recommended for an optimal experience.
name: Shell Key Preserve
address: 2187 Oceanview Dr, Tierra Verde, FL 33715, USA

excerpt: Lakeside park featuring scenic views, tennis courts, a baseball field, playgrounds & a dog park.
detail_description: Crescent Lake Park is a popular lakeside destination in the city, offering scenic views, tennis courts, a baseball field, playgrounds for kids of all ages, and a dedicated dog park. The park's central location and ample space make it a favorite among locals and visitors alike. Families can enjoy picnics by the lake or take leisurely strolls along the trail while keeping an eye out for geese.
name: Crescent Lake Park
address: 1320 5th St N, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Relaxed Pass-a-Grille is known for Pass-a-Grille Beach, a wide stretch of white sand along the Gulf Coast. Beach boutiques and casual seafood spots and bars cluster nearby, especially along 8th Avenue. The Gulf Beaches Historical Museum traces the region’s past through memorabilia like photographs and old postcards. Boat tours to secluded Shell Key Preserve depart from Merry Pier, also a popular fishing spot.
detail_description: Pass-a-Grille Beach is a wide stretch of white sand along the Gulf Coast, offering a relaxed atmosphere and beautiful sunset views. The area features beach boutiques, casual seafood spots, and bars along 8th Avenue. Visitors can explore the Gulf Beaches Historical Museum to learn about the region's past or take boat tours to secluded Shell Key Preserve from Merry Pier. This location is less crowded than other nearby beaches, providing easy parking and peaceful surroundings for capturing perfect photos of the sunset.
name: Pass-a-Grille Beach
address: St Pete Beach, FL 33706, USA

excerpt: Showcase for contemporary works by US & international glass artists, with a lush sculpture garden.
detail_description: The Duncan McClellan Gallery is a unique showcase for contemporary glass art by both US and international artists, set in a former fish and tomato packing facility. The 7,800 square feet of exhibition space features rotating exhibitions that highlight the work of leading glass artisans. Visitors can also witness live demonstrations at the hot shop where artisans create their latest masterpieces. The gallery's lush sculpture garden adds to the overall experience, making it a must-visit destination for art enthusiasts.
name: Duncan McClellan Gallery
address: 2342 Emerson Ave S, St. Petersburg, FL 33712, USA

excerpt: Swamp conservation area with a mile-long boardwalk & a 1/2-mile dirt path for wildlife observation.
detail_description: Sawgrass Lake Park is one of the most popular attractions in St. Petersburg. The park spans 400 acres and features a mile-long elevated boardwalk with options for wildlife observation. The park also has canals and lakes perfect for fishing, as well as a half-mile dirt trail for hiking or biking.
name: Sawgrass Lake Park
address: 7400 25th St N, St. Petersburg, FL 33702, USA

excerpt: Regional theater presenting year-round plays in a modern space, plus a springtime park production.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Downtown St. Petersburg, the American Stage Theatre Company has been a cultural gem since its inception in 1977. This vibrant regional theater offers an array of year-round performances in its modern Raymond James Theatre, which seats 182 guests comfortably. Each spring, audiences can also enjoy the delightful American Stage in the Park production, adding a unique outdoor experience to their theatrical journey.
name: American Stage Theatre Company_L00239442
address: 163 3rd St N, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

detail_description: Located in St. Petersburg, Florida, the Florida Orange Groves Winery has been a part of the community since the 1970s. Initially known for shipping fresh citrus, it has now transitioned into producing 43 varieties of fruit wines. This family-owned business offers a wide range of tropical, citrus, and berry wines for visitors to taste and purchase.
name: Florida Orange Groves Winery
address: 1500 Pasadena Ave S, South Pasadena, FL 33707, USA

excerpt: Familiar plays, new musicals & offbeat productions performed on a modest regional theater stage.
detail_description: freeFall Theatre offers a diverse range of performances, from familiar plays to new musicals and offbeat productions. Visitors have praised the stellar one-man performance in "Love to Eat," as well as the exceptional treatment by the Operations Manager when there was an issue with tickets. The theater's holiday show, "The Night Before," has been described as the best in the area, with hilarious moments and phenomenal music.
name: freeFall Theatre
address: 6099 Central Ave, St. Petersburg, FL 33710, USA

excerpt: Elegant space, with box seats & a waterfront view, hosts the Florida Orchestra & other events.
detail_description: Duke Energy Center for the Arts - Mahaffey Theater is a theater in downtown Saint Petersburg, Florida that offers a variety of events. The theater has comfortable box seats and a waterfront view which makes it an excellent place to see live music or theatrical performances.
name: Duke Energy Center for the Arts - Mahaffey Theater
address: 400 1st St S, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Year-round greyhound race track, poker tournaments & an American restaurant with dinner buffets.
detail_description: Win! Derby at Historic Derby Lane St Petersburg is a year-round destination offering greyhound racing, poker tournaments, and an American restaurant with dinner buffets. While live greyhound racing has been banned due to Amendment 13, visitors can still enjoy simulcasts of races from across the nation. The venue does not offer electronic gaming devices but provides an unforgettable experience with gourmet dining options and craft drinks.
name: Win! Derby at Historic Derby Lane St Petersburg
address: 10490 Gandy Blvd N, St. Petersburg, FL 33702, USA

excerpt: A 24-hour fishing pier across Tampa Bay offering sunset views & a myriad of saltwater fish species.
detail_description: The Skyway Fishing Pier State Park is a popular fishing spot located on the north and south sides of Tampa Bay. The pier stretches 4 miles into the bay, and offers excellent views of the sunset and diverse species of fish that can be caught 24/7.
name: N Skyway Fishing Pier State Park
address: I-275, St. Petersburg, FL 33711, USA

excerpt: City park with a playground, picnic shelter, boat ramps & restrooms beside the water.
detail_description: Demens Landing Park is a waterfront green space located in St. Petersburg, Florida. It was built on the site of the city's first railway pier and offers various amenities such as a playground, picnic shelter, boat ramps, and restrooms. The park spans 14.7 acres and is nestled between two yacht basins, providing stunning views of Tampa Bay and the New Pier.
name: Demens Landing Park
address: Bayshore Dr. & 2nd Ave. S, 525-549 2nd Ave SE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: A vast array of palms from around the world are displayed in this tranquil park-based arboretum.
detail_description: Gizella Kopsick Palm Arboretum, located just north of Vinoy Park in St. Petersburg, is a serene 2-acre waterfront park showcasing over 500 palms and cycads from around the world. The lush tropical gardens were once a mini-golf course but have been transformed into a tranquil oasis with winding red brick paths, open green spaces for picnics, gazebos, benches, and drinking fountains.
name: Gizella Kopsick Palm Arboretum
address: 605 11th Ave NE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Grand brick performing-arts center in a circa-1925 former church presenting plays, films & more.
detail_description: The Palladium Theater in St. Petersburg is a grand performing arts center housed in a former church dating back to 1925. The venue consists of two spaces: the 850-seat Hough Hall and the intimate 175-seat The Side Door cabaret, both known for hosting a wide range of performances including classical, jazz, blues, rock, country, opera, dance, comedy and literary events.
name: Palladium at St. Petersburg College
address: 253 5th Ave N, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

detail_description: Al Lang Stadium, located at 230 First St. S., is a unique soccer venue with an electric atmosphere during Rowdies games. The field setup allows fans to be directly behind one of the goals, creating an ideal environment for bothering visiting goalies. The stadium is well-maintained and offers easy parking options, including on-street parking and nearby garages. Additionally, it hosts a weekend farmer's market and benefits from a refreshing breeze due to its proximity to the water.
name: Al Lang Stadium
address: 230 1st St SE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: This 70-acre oceanside park features a covered playground, boat ramps, an Indian midden site & more.
detail_description: Maximo Park, located in South St. Pete, spans 70 acres and offers a variety of recreational activities for visitors. The park features three boat ramps, nature boardwalks, beach-side playgrounds, bike and nature trails through wooded areas, and an 18-hole disc golf course. Additionally, the park boasts an observation tower providing stunning views of the Sunshine Skyway Bridge, the Gulf of Mexico, and Boca Ciega Bay.
name: Maximo Park
address: Pinellas Point Dr S &, Sunshine Skyway Ln S, St. Petersburg, FL 33711, USA

excerpt: Green space with monuments honoring soldiers, plus a waterside boardwalk, canoe trail & boat ramp.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of St. Petersburg, War Veterans Memorial Park is a serene green space that pays tribute to the brave men and women who served in the U.S. Armed Forces. This park features impressive monuments dedicated to each military branch, including a poignant battlefield cross honoring local Gulf War heroes. Visitors can enjoy stunning views of the Bayou while strolling along its waterside boardwalk or exploring the canoe trail and double boat ramp, perfect for water enthusiasts.
name: War Veterans Memorial Park
address: 9600 Bay Pines Blvd, St. Petersburg, FL 33708, USA

detail_description: The Museum of the American Arts and Crafts Movement, located in St. Petersburg, FL, is a unique institution dedicated to showcasing the American Arts and Crafts movement. After over five years of construction delays, this museum will finally open its doors as the world's first museum solely focused on this artistic shift.
name: Museum of the American Arts and Crafts Movement
address: 355 4th St N, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

detail_description: Nestled in downtown St. Petersburg, Pinellas Ale Works Brewery, affectionately known as PAW, is a renowned dog-friendly establishment that offers an array of craft beers such as the CocoMutt and Howlin. The brewery hosts live music events and fundraisers for local animal charities in Pinellas County. With its extensive tap list and ever-changing offerings, PAW provides a vibrant atmosphere with activities like trivia nights and dog-themed parties.
name: Pinellas Ale Works Brewery
address: 1962 1st Ave S, St. Petersburg, FL 33712, USA

detail_description: Nestled at the southern end of St. Petersburg's vibrant downtown seafront, Albert Whitted Park is a delightful oasis that pays tribute to local aviation pioneer James Albert Whitted. This charming park features expansive grassy areas perfect for lounging, along with a modern children's playground designed with an airplane theme, making it an exciting spot for families. The park also offers covered picnic shelters and clean solar-powered restrooms, ensuring a comfortable visit.
name: Albert Whitted Park
address: 480 Bayshore Dr SE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

detail_description: Pioneer Park is located in downtown St. Petersburg, FL and honors 600 early settlers of the city. The park is conveniently situated between the St. Petersburg Yacht Club and Al Lang Stadium and offers a lovely shaded city park experience with great views of Tampa Bay. It's a great place to take a break from the hustle and bustle of downtown or for just enjoying some sun and fresh air.
name: Pioneer Park
address: 50-98 Bayshore Dr SE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

detail_description: The Tampa Bay Watch Discovery Center offers an intriguing exhibit called "Snakes of the Estuary," showcasing native snakes and their ecological importance. The center also provides insight into the estuary's history and conservation efforts, highlighting its pivotal role in the area. Visitors can enjoy interactive experiences such as feeding seahorses and interacting with marine creatures in a touch tank. Additionally, they can join engaging eco tours led by knowledgeable marine biologists to further explore the surrounding wildlife.
name: Tampa Bay Watch Discovery Center
address: 700 2nd Ave NE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

detail_description: I visited the St. Petersburg region and attended an early Sunday morning mass at the Catholic church Cathedral of St. Jude the Apostle. The church is incredibly stunning, rivaling even St. Johns Cathedral in Savannah, with its blend of modernity and old world charm. I had a chance to speak with the approachable priest after the service and expressed my interest in learning about the church's history during my next visit.
name: Cathedral of St. Jude the Apostle
address: 5815 5th Ave N, St. Petersburg, FL 33710, USA

excerpt: Recreational green space on 7.3 acres by the marina, featuring walking trails & a scenic fountain.
detail_description: South Straub Park is a lovely green space with walking trails and a scenic fountain located in the St. Pete downtown waterfront. It's perfect for a morning stroll and provides residents with a great place to relax and enjoy the cityscape. Across the street are outdoor cafes to savor your breakfast or lunch!
name: South Straub Park
address: 198 Bayshore Dr NE, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA

excerpt: Gallery for local crafts, with a gift shop & a cafe serving light fare, in an Arts & Crafts home.
detail_description: Craftsman House - Gallery, Cafe & Pottery Studio is a restored Craftsman bungalow that offers an all-encompassing cultural experience. It houses a local crafts gallery, gift shop, charming cafe, and functioning pottery studio. The establishment also features a weekly radio show and serves as a music venue. Visitors can explore the art-filled rooms while enjoying light fare at the cafe or browsing through the unique pottery pieces in the studio's gift shop.
name: Craftsman House - Gallery, Cafe & Pottery Studio
address: 2955 Central Ave, St. Petersburg, FL 33713, USA

excerpt: Unique store offering accessories made by owner Wilmer Vergara & other artisans, plus local artwork.
detail_description: Graphi-ko Gallery, Crystals & Jewelry is a distinctive shop that showcases unique accessories crafted by proprietor Wilmer Vergara and other skilled artisans, alongside local artwork. Their collection of stones is extensive and reasonably priced. A beautifully arranged table near the register exhibits various stone points that are available for purchase. The store's spacious layout accommodates individuals using mobility scooters, with wheelchair accessibility at the entrance. The wide selection includes not only different types of stones but also varying sizes.
name: Graphi-ko Gallery, Crystals & Jewelry
address: 669 Central Ave, St. Petersburg, FL 33701, USA
